  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Displacement Tracking, CCCM Light, and Direct Humanitarian Assistance Provision</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to improve, indirectly, the camps of 106,000 internally displaced persons in the Central African Republic. IOM and its partners will use CERF funds to train 60 aid workers on IOM&apos;s Displacement Tracking Matrix so that they can use DTM tools for better site management and to use specific tools at 25 sites. IOM and its partners will also establish a database to record the humanitarian needs of and protection cases among displaced people, and establish referral mechanisms. The project will be implemented within 9 months.</narrative>
  </description>
